{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 13:07:32.560998", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"ospf_area_misconfiguration\"]\n\nRationale (brief):\n- The server_access_router is advertising 10.200.0.0/24 into OSPF (running-config shows \"network 10.200.0.0/24 area 0\" and the route is directly connected), causing backend web servers to be routable from user subnets. This is a configuration/policy misconfiguration of OSPF advertisement (ospf_area_misconfiguration) and constitutes the design-policy anomaly reported.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2665, "output_tokens": 135, "total_tokens": 2800, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
